node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Nike Skateboarding on July 17, 2021 tagging @pietparra, @taka_nu, @ryomotohashi, @n.t.original, @joshuanishimiya, @uruseeeeeee___, and @itsme_juliana_. May be an image of 6 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
There’s no uniform for skateboarding or one defining aesthetic. So for artist and skateboarder Piet Parra, designing the Nike SB Federation Kits was a challenge to create a unified look that spoke to skating’s imaginative spirit.

“There’s tremendous respect for the countries and colors of their flags. I just tried to find a complementary set of colors to match. This way it still resembles the flags but also complements other natural colors that might occur in the countries landscapes and cities.” — @pietparra on the color and inspiration of the kits
⁠⁠
Available today in select skate shops and July 20 in SNKRS. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Learn more at NikeSB.com⁠⁠
⁠⁠
@ikeda__daisuke @ryomotohashi @joshuanishimiya @isseimorinaka @n.t.original @taka_nu @uruseeeeeee___ @itsme_juliana_⁠⁠

#NikeSB | 📷 @10npei @atsuu⁠⁠

node.text:
Featuring pristine white and crystal blue as the foundation,@ftc_skateboarding adds enamel detailing, a clear sole, and a pop of yellow to the SB Dunk Low, a reflection of Japanese public bathhouses known as sentōs where communities refresh, recharge, and soak up culture.⁠
⁠
Releasing today at @ftcsanfrancisco and starting July 19 in select skate shops and SNKRS.⁠
⁠
Learn more at NikeSB.com

node.text:
Since 1986, @ftc_skateboarding has been more than a skate shop—it’s the epitome of how far skate culture can reach. A burgeoning scene fueled by creativity and swagger in San Francisco, California was the spark; a street skating renaissance in the ‘90s made it the Mecca; and with shops in Barcelona, Spain and Toyko, Japan, “For the City” has gone global.⁠
⁠
Stop by one of the shops if you’re in the area:⁠
⁠
FTC San Francisco⁠
1632 Haight Street⁠
San Francisco, CA 94117 ⁠
@ftcsanfrancisco⁠
⁠
FTC Tokyo⁠
5-28-7 Jingumae Shibuya-ku⁠
Tokyo Japan 150-0001⁠
@ftcjp⁠
⁠
FTC Nagoya⁠
5-18-30 Sakae Naka-ku⁠
Nagoya, Japan 460-0008⁠
⁠
FTC Osaka⁠
1-8-3 Minami Horie Nishi-ku⁠
Osaka, Japan 550-0015⁠
⁠
FTC Barcelona⁠
Valldonzella 3 08001⁠
Barcelona, ​​Spain⁠
@ftcbarcelona

#NikeSB | 🗣 @ratt_ray

node.text:
Sandy Bodecker’s career with Nike was defined by vision, innovation, and challenging possibility. That spirit translated further than soles—it was the soul of Nike SB from the beginning. The Sandy Bodecker ZoomX Bruin is an homage to his belief that skateboarding should be heralded across the spectrum of sport and its elite would one day compete on the world stage.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The ZoomX Bruin crystalizes a milestone, melding an iconic silhouette with Sandy Bodecker’s unbridled vibrance and vision. From the insole detailing to the sublimated graphic FLYKNIT treatment inspired by the portrait of the SB architect himself, the Sandy ZoomX Bruin was made for the moment.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Learn more at NikeSB.com.
